00:22:41.810 --> 00:22:44.730 line:82%
I haven't seen you before.
You're not from our college.

232
00:22:45.590 --> 00:22:47.709 line:82%
You are right.
I'm here with somebody.

233
00:22:47.970 --> 00:22:51.440 line:82%
Would you care to dance with me?

234
00:22:52.530 --> 00:22:54.584 line:82%
I'm sorry.
The fact is that Rohit and I...

235
00:22:54.700 --> 00:22:57.667 line:82%
Rohit? I see,
you are Rohit's sister?

236
00:22:57.780 --> 00:23:00.000 line:82%
- No, actually I...
- Don't be silly.

237
00:23:00.120 --> 00:23:02.167 line:82%
Rohit and I are close friends.

238
00:23:02.250 --> 00:23:05.417 line:82%
In fact, he's like a brother to me.

239
00:23:05.500 --> 00:23:06.750 line:82%
Just one dance.

240
00:23:07.490 --> 00:23:09.420 line:82%
I'm really sorry.
I can't.

241
00:23:10.590 --> 00:23:15.417 line:82%
Not even if I told you
that I love you?

242
00:23:15.510 --> 00:23:16.720 line:82%
Excuse me!

243
00:23:18.350 --> 00:23:21.917 line:82%
Yes, Shalini.
I love you and only you.

244
00:23:22.000 --> 00:23:23.542 line:82%
My every breath,

245
00:23:23.625 --> 00:23:28.270 line:82%
every heartbeat is filled
with you, Shalini.

246
00:23:29.110 --> 00:23:32.769 line:82%
I'm sure I was born to love you.

247
00:23:33.070 --> 00:23:36.334 line:82%
And you were born to be mine.

248
00:23:36.450 --> 00:23:40.040 line:82%
You are mine, Shalini,
and if you ask your heart,

249
00:23:40.620 --> 00:23:43.580 line:82%
you'll realize I'm speaking the truth.

250
00:23:44.750 --> 00:23:47.460 line:82%
- Wow!
- Bravo!

251
00:23:57.760 --> 00:23:58.800 line:82%
Hey...

252
00:23:59.680 --> 00:24:01.470 line:82%
Excuse me. Who are you?

253
00:24:02.010 --> 00:24:03.770 line:82%
Don't you recognize your brother, Rohit?

254
00:24:07.100 --> 00:24:10.940 line:82%
You're Rohit?
I mean, you're Rohit, too?

255
00:24:11.480 --> 00:24:12.500 line:82%
I'm so sorry!

256
00:24:12.610 --> 00:24:14.970 line:82%
I thought Shalini was
another Rohit's sister.

257
00:24:15.650 --> 00:24:17.320 line:82%
Look at him. He's over there.

258
00:24:19.660 --> 00:24:21.660 line:82%
- Hi, Sameer.
- Hey, Rohit.

259
00:24:27.500 --> 00:24:30.910 line:82%
Sameer? Your name's Sameer?

260
00:24:31.490 --> 00:24:35.770 line:82%
So, you've been lying to me
all these days? That's not good.

261
00:24:38.050 --> 00:24:39.167 line:82%
Well...

262
00:24:39.260 --> 00:24:41.625 line:82%
I don't know what to say.
You can see for yourself.

263
00:24:41.720 --> 00:24:44.180 line:82%
He has been lying to me
that he's Rohit.

264
00:24:44.740 --> 00:24:48.270 line:82%
He is not Rohit,
and Shalini is not my sister.

265
00:24:49.690 --> 00:24:51.190 line:82%
Shalini is my fiancee.

266
00:24:53.360 --> 00:24:54.650 line:82%
Fiancee?

267
00:24:57.440 --> 00:25:01.280 line:82%
You know, Sameer, I don't like
you being friends with Akash.

268
00:25:02.280 --> 00:25:06.370 line:82%
The way he behaved the other
night was so embarrassing.

269
00:25:07.450 --> 00:25:10.460 line:82%
Let him go his way.
Just keep away from him.

270
00:25:11.960 --> 00:25:14.584 line:82%
- But Akash is my friend, Priya.
- Come off it, Sameer.

271
00:25:14.670 --> 00:25:17.010 line:82%
Have you no other friends besides Akash?

272
00:25:18.260 --> 00:25:20.834 line:82%
- Of course, but...
- Just decide, Sameer.

273
00:25:20.930 --> 00:25:23.430 line:82%
Either be friends with Akash or with me.

274
00:25:27.090 --> 00:25:28.180 line:82%
Sameer?

275
00:25:29.680 --> 00:25:31.042 line:82%
I'm thinking about it.

276
00:25:31.150 --> 00:25:34.375 line:82%
You need time to think
if you want to be with me?

277
00:25:34.480 --> 00:25:36.030 line:82%
How insensitive, Sameer!

278
00:25:37.430 --> 00:25:41.390 line:82%
- So, you need some time?
- No, I mean...

279
00:25:41.990 --> 00:25:43.084 line:82%
Don't be silly, Priya.

280
00:25:43.200 --> 00:25:46.542 line:82%
I'm going out with my friends.
I'll be home by two.

281
00:25:46.660 --> 00:25:51.390 line:82%
If I don't hear from you by
then, I'll know your answer.

282
00:25:53.330 --> 00:25:54.380 line:82%
Priya.

283
00:25:55.930 --> 00:25:58.420 line:82%
Aren't you taking this too seriously?

284
00:26:00.720 --> 00:26:03.970 line:82%
No, I'm not that serious yet.

285
00:26:05.010 --> 00:26:07.890 line:82%
But, if I do get serious,
then God help you!

286
00:26:30.010 --> 00:26:31.375 line:82%
What are you doing?

287
00:26:31.460 --> 00:26:33.870 line:82%
Your bruise has a funny color.

288
00:26:34.230 --> 00:26:36.542 line:82%
Sid, have you had a look?

289
00:26:36.650 --> 00:26:38.542 line:82%
Do you like it?
You want one, too?

290
00:26:38.630 --> 00:26:40.000 line:82%
Hey!

291
00:26:40.240 --> 00:26:42.460 line:82%
Don't vent it out on me.

292
00:26:42.740 --> 00:26:44.584 line:82%
Did I ask you to talk to Shalini?

293
00:26:44.670 --> 00:26:47.260 line:82%
No, but you could've helped me.

294
00:26:47.810 --> 00:26:48.810 line:82%
Hey, you.

295
00:26:48.900 --> 00:26:51.930 line:82%
You just sat there.
Some friend you are!

296
00:26:52.510 --> 00:26:55.760 line:82%
Better to be friends with Rohit.
At least he'll protect me.

297
00:26:57.990 --> 00:27:00.690 line:82%
God bless your friendship.
I'm leaving.

298
00:27:01.080 --> 00:27:03.209 line:82%
- Where to?
- Home.

299
00:27:03.330 --> 00:27:05.375 line:82%
Sit down. What's the hurry?
Right, Sameer?

300
00:27:05.470 --> 00:27:07.540 line:82%
Yes, man, it's one in the afternoon.

301
00:27:09.120 --> 00:27:11.480 line:82%
Which country are you in?
It's almost four!

302
00:27:28.210 --> 00:27:29.600 line:82%
Oh, my God!

303
00:27:30.050 --> 00:27:31.890 line:82%
I forgot to call Priya.

304
00:27:33.010 --> 00:27:34.730 line:82%
She's going to kill me.

305
00:27:35.340 --> 00:27:36.709 line:82%
Why are you so scared of Priya?

306
00:27:36.820 --> 00:27:38.792 line:82%
I'm not scared of her.
I love her.

307
00:27:38.880 --> 00:27:41.690 line:82%
I don't want to hurt her, or lose her.

308
00:27:42.070 --> 00:27:45.790 line:82%
Sameer, I just don't understand
how you even tolerate her.

309
00:27:45.980 --> 00:27:48.070 line:82%
She's more of a boss than a girlfriend.

310
00:27:48.810 --> 00:27:52.700 line:82%
Akash, I need help,
not your expert comments.

311
00:27:52.900 --> 00:27:53.910 line:82%
What should I do now?

312
00:27:54.700 --> 00:27:56.040 line:82%
What do you think?

313
00:27:56.390 --> 00:27:59.060 line:82%
I'll tell you.
Call Priya and apologize.

314
00:27:59.530 --> 00:28:01.810 line:82%
Say you'll never be friends with me again.

315
00:28:01.910 --> 00:28:04.270 line:82%
Shut up, Akash.
You know I won't do that.

316
00:28:04.570 --> 00:28:08.260 line:82%
What if she gets hurts
or you lose her? Christ!

317
00:28:09.790 --> 00:28:11.490 line:82%
You'll never change, will you?

318
00:28:12.600 --> 00:28:16.020 line:82%
Sameer, don't make a big deal out of it.

319
00:28:16.460 --> 00:28:18.900 line:82%
Just relax. Relax.

320
00:28:19.420 --> 00:28:22.084 line:82%
Call her and talk to her.
It'll be fine.

321
00:28:22.170 --> 00:28:24.834 line:82%
- Okay?
- Okay.

322
00:28:24.920 --> 00:28:25.920 line:82%
Okay.

323
00:28:42.430 --> 00:28:43.750 line:82%
Hi, Priya.

324
00:28:44.760 --> 00:28:46.375 line:82%
I was... but...

325
00:28:46.480 --> 00:28:48.292 line:82%
Hear me out... but you...

326
00:28:48.390 --> 00:28:50.440 line:82%
But... when...

327
00:28:51.790 --> 00:28:54.560 line:82%
I'm at Akash's. Hello...?

328
00:28:58.360 --> 00:28:59.430 line:82%
She hung up.

329
00:29:00.160 --> 00:29:02.880 line:82%
Did you expect her to say
"Sorry, darling?"

330
00:29:03.610 --> 00:29:04.792 line:82%
What nonsense!

331
00:29:05.100 --> 00:29:06.875 line:82%
There's a limit to everything, Sameer.

332
00:29:06.990 --> 00:29:10.000 line:82%
Tell her these tantrums won't work.

333
00:29:10.350 --> 00:29:13.917 line:82%
She'll have to do as you say
if she wants to be with you.

334
00:29:14.180 --> 00:29:15.875 line:82%
She's challenged your self-respect.

335
00:29:15.980 --> 00:29:18.260 line:82%
What are you doing? Be a man!

336
00:29:19.010 --> 00:29:20.120 line:82%
Yeah?

337
00:29:20.720 --> 00:29:21.720 line:82%
Yeah.

338
00:29:22.120 --> 00:29:23.240 line:82%
Yeah!

339
00:29:23.960 --> 00:29:26.625 line:82%
You're absolutely right, Akash.
That's what I'll do now.

340
00:29:26.730 --> 00:29:28.290 line:82%
- That's like a man.
- See you later.

341
00:29:28.600 --> 00:29:30.350 line:82%
- Bye, Sid.
- Just give it to her!

342
00:29:39.830 --> 00:29:41.130 line:82%
He'll have it now.

343
00:29:45.320 --> 00:29:47.370 line:82%
- Hello?
- Hello, Akash?

344
00:29:47.860 --> 00:29:49.084 line:82%
- Priya?
- Yes.

345
00:29:49.410 --> 00:29:51.875 line:82%
- Put Sameer on the phone.
- He hasn't been here.

346
00:29:51.970 --> 00:29:53.500 line:82%
I haven't seen him
since last night.

347
00:29:53.584 --> 00:29:56.000 line:82%
What? He hasn't been there?
What the hell...

348
00:29:56.290 --> 00:29:59.040 line:82%
Watch it! You almost hit my other eye.

349
00:30:13.120 --> 00:30:15.260 line:82%
- I want to talk to you.
- No need.

350
00:30:15.780 --> 00:30:17.270 line:82%
I know what you have to say.

351
00:30:17.950 --> 00:30:19.300 line:82%
- Do you?
- Yes, I do.

352
00:30:19.650 --> 00:30:21.880 line:82%
I called up Akash after talking to you.

353
00:30:22.460 --> 00:30:23.584 line:82%
So?

354
00:30:23.690 --> 00:30:25.810 line:82%
He said you weren't at his house.

355
00:30:26.090 --> 00:30:28.584 line:82%
- What!
- Don't pretend, Sameer.

356
00:30:28.690 --> 00:30:32.230 line:82%
I can't believe this. I never
knew you're such a big liar.

357
00:30:32.470 --> 00:30:34.480 line:82%
But now, enough is enough!

358
00:30:34.730 --> 00:30:36.900 line:82%
I don't want to see your face again.

359
00:30:37.150 --> 00:30:38.490 line:82%
Go to hell!

360
00:31:05.970 --> 00:31:06.970 line:82%
Excuse me.

361
00:31:10.210 --> 00:31:11.650 line:82%
May I help you?

362
00:31:12.390 --> 00:31:14.010 line:82%
No, it's okay. Thank you.

363
00:31:14.960 --> 00:31:16.530 line:82%
No problem. It's not that far.

364
00:31:17.630 --> 00:31:21.080 line:82%
No, it's okay. Thank you.
Thank you very much.

365
00:31:27.000 --> 00:31:28.200 line:82%
Gosh!

366
00:31:30.920 --> 00:31:32.250 line:82%
Shit!

367
00:31:34.870 --> 00:31:36.180 line:82%
Shit!

368
00:31:55.950 --> 00:31:57.070 line:82%
Thanks.

369
00:32:01.340 --> 00:32:03.375 line:82%
- God! What's in there?
- My things.

370
00:32:03.490 --> 00:32:05.370 line:82%
No, wait. I'll hold here.

371
00:32:27.270 --> 00:32:28.390 line:82%
Phew!

372
00:32:31.060 --> 00:32:35.125 line:82%
That was just one suitcase
and we're already tired...

373
00:32:35.230 --> 00:32:36.800 line:82%
Only two more.

374
00:32:37.390 --> 00:32:40.190 line:82%
Only two? Let's go.

375
00:32:55.670 --> 00:32:56.920 line:82%
Oh!

376
00:33:03.510 --> 00:33:04.760 line:82%
A nice place.

377
00:33:07.560 --> 00:33:08.600 line:82%
Thank you.

378
00:33:10.230 --> 00:33:13.230 line:82%
It belongs to the company I work for.

379
00:33:15.930 --> 00:33:19.040 line:82%
I'm an interior designer.
I'm Tara Jaiswal.

380
00:33:20.280 --> 00:33:21.890 line:82%
- Siddharth Sinha.
- Hi.

381
00:33:22.280 --> 00:33:23.530 line:82%
Sid.

382
00:33:24.410 --> 00:33:25.620 line:82%
What do you do?

383
00:33:26.910 --> 00:33:29.330 line:82%
On Sundays I work as a porter.

384
00:33:31.540 --> 00:33:33.000 line:82%
And what about the weekdays?

385
00:33:33.410 --> 00:33:36.630 line:82%
When people ask I say the first
thing that comes to my mind.

386
00:33:37.110 --> 00:33:40.370 line:82%
But I'll tell you the truth as
I think it might interest you.

387
00:33:41.840 --> 00:33:42.875 line:82%
What do you mean?

388
00:33:42.980 --> 00:33:46.720 line:82%
You have three paintings among
your things. That's what I do.

389
00:33:47.240 --> 00:33:48.300 line:82%
I'm a painter.

390
00:33:48.920 --> 00:33:50.417 line:82%
- Really?
- Yes.

391
00:33:50.520 --> 00:33:51.980 line:82%
How exciting!

392
00:33:53.180 --> 00:33:54.970 line:82%
May I see your paintings?

393
00:33:56.230 --> 00:33:57.360 line:82%
Of course.

394
00:33:57.980 --> 00:33:59.190 line:82%
Where do you live?

395
00:33:59.510 --> 00:34:01.190 line:82%
The last house down this road.

396
00:34:02.020 --> 00:34:03.350 line:82%
You're welcome any time.

397
00:34:06.780 --> 00:34:10.240 line:82%
- Sid, I'm off to the office.
- Just a minute, Mom.

398
00:34:11.219 --> 00:34:15.360 line:82%
I'm also coming along.
You can drop me off at Sameer's.

399
00:34:18.000 --> 00:34:21.174 line:82%
Listen, it's Anju's wedding
anniversary today.

400
00:34:21.310 --> 00:34:23.199 line:82%
She'll be upset if you don't come.

401
00:34:28.710 --> 00:34:30.500 line:82%
- Hello.
- Hello.

402
00:34:30.610 --> 00:34:33.020 line:82%
- Is Siddharth at home?
- Yes.

403
00:34:33.750 --> 00:34:36.050 line:82%
- You are...?
- I'm Tara.

404
00:34:37.120 --> 00:34:39.780 line:82%
Hi. Please come in.

405
00:34:40.909 --> 00:34:42.334 line:82%
Mom, this is Tara.

406
00:34:42.440 --> 00:34:44.050 line:82%
- Hi.
- Hi.

407
00:34:45.820 --> 00:34:47.542 line:82%
So, shall I go?

408
00:34:47.650 --> 00:34:49.875 line:82%
Yes, I'll go later.

409
00:34:49.969 --> 00:34:52.209 line:82%
Fine. But you'll come
this evening, won't you?

410
00:34:52.330 --> 00:34:55.000 line:82%
- Where?
- To Anju's.

411
00:34:56.380 --> 00:34:57.930 line:82%
It's boring there.

412
00:34:59.580 --> 00:35:02.430 line:82%
There are very few places
that you don't find boring.

413
00:35:02.580 --> 00:35:04.420 line:82%
Fine. Don't come.

414
00:35:05.340 --> 00:35:06.690 line:82%
- Bye.
- Bye.

415
00:35:10.020 --> 00:35:11.350 line:82%
Please sit down.

416
00:35:12.920 --> 00:35:14.680 line:82%
I'd like to see your paintings first.

417
00:35:53.450 --> 00:35:54.890 line:82%
The same thing again.

418
00:35:57.160 --> 00:35:58.560 line:82%
What thing?

419
00:36:00.280 --> 00:36:02.650 line:82%
I've learned something about you today.

420
00:36:05.375 --> 00:36:09.750 line:82%
Something I didn't see when we first met.

421
00:36:11.780 --> 00:36:13.080 line:82%
What's that?

422
00:36:17.080 --> 00:36:20.330 line:82%
You meet people and interact with them.

423
00:36:21.280 --> 00:36:24.360 line:82%
But there's a world within you

424
00:36:25.180 --> 00:36:27.710 line:82%
which is made of your dreams
and fantasies.

425
00:36:29.240 --> 00:36:32.560 line:82%
You don't share them with anyone.

426
00:36:35.120 --> 00:36:39.400 line:82%
I wonder if those who claim to know you

427
00:36:41.050 --> 00:36:42.520 line:82%
really know you at all.

428
00:36:46.610 --> 00:36:47.960 line:82%
What makes you say that?

429
00:36:52.440 --> 00:36:55.420 line:82%
The door is closed.
No one can enter it.

430
00:36:55.880 --> 00:36:59.500 line:82%
The box is shut.
No one can steal anything.

431
00:37:01.700 --> 00:37:06.590 line:82%
Who can say what feelings
lie behind those eyelids?

432
00:37:08.287 --> 00:37:13.130 line:82%
I wonder what other things
your paintings hide.

433
00:37:16.580 --> 00:37:18.400 line:82%
Perhaps like the way you do.

434
00:37:22.290 --> 00:37:23.940 line:82%
What are you looking at?

435
00:37:25.650 --> 00:37:27.910 line:82%
Which painting do you like the best?

436
00:37:30.830 --> 00:37:32.490 line:82%
I haven't painted it yet.

437
00:38:07.040 --> 00:38:09.640 line:82%
- Hey!
- Jesus!

438
00:38:10.830 --> 00:38:11.830 line:82%
Akash.

439
00:38:14.200 --> 00:38:15.970 line:82%
You scared the hell out of me, man.

440
00:38:16.200 --> 00:38:18.790 line:82%
Your face is as white as the bed sheet.

441
00:38:21.190 --> 00:38:22.649 line:82%
I'm very angry right now.

442
00:38:22.840 --> 00:38:24.660 line:82%
- All because of you.
- Why?

443
00:38:24.910 --> 00:38:27.280 line:82%
Man, I saved your life
and you're angry with me?

444
00:38:27.480 --> 00:38:29.570 line:82%
- Saved my life?
- Absolutely!

445
00:38:29.740 --> 00:38:31.120 line:82%
It had to happen.

446
00:38:31.180 --> 00:38:32.960 line:82%
Priya would've ditched you one day.

447
00:38:33.050 --> 00:38:34.167 line:82%
You know why?

448
00:38:34.230 --> 00:38:37.350 line:82%
She didn't love you,
but some other Sameer.

449
00:38:37.890 --> 00:38:40.380 line:82%
He looked like you,
but he was someone else.

450
00:38:40.930 --> 00:38:42.709 line:82%
You're not that Sameer.
You're our Sameer.

451
00:38:42.820 --> 00:38:44.840 line:82%
Sid and I know you

452
00:38:44.950 --> 00:38:47.090 line:82%
and Priya can only hope to know you.

453
00:38:47.830 --> 00:38:50.850 line:82%
If you became Priya's Sameer,
our Sameer would be the loser.

454
00:38:53.040 --> 00:38:55.550 line:82%
- I never thought of it that way.
- I know.

455
00:38:56.780 --> 00:38:58.439 line:82%
- I feel much better.
- Good.

456
00:38:58.810 --> 00:39:00.417 line:82%
Then pack your bag and come with us.

457
00:39:00.530 --> 00:39:02.250 line:82%
Sid and I are waiting for you in the car.

458
00:39:02.370 --> 00:39:04.040 line:82%
- Where are we going?
- Goa.

459
00:39:04.600 --> 00:39:05.600 line:82%
