chika pika rola rika

927
01:21:07.380 --> 01:21:08.540 line:82%
Ram pam posh...

928
01:21:13.130 --> 01:21:14.340 line:82%
Good night!

929
01:21:18.380 --> 01:21:20.390 line:82%
Sid, you're home. Good night.

930
01:21:22.060 --> 01:21:23.230 line:82%
I love her.

931
01:21:24.810 --> 01:21:25.980 line:82%
What?

932
01:21:26.890 --> 01:21:27.980 line:82%
Yes.

933
01:21:29.520 --> 01:21:30.900 line:82%
I love her, Akash.

934
01:21:33.110 --> 01:21:34.530 line:82%
You're joking, right?

935
01:21:39.530 --> 01:21:40.990 line:82%
No, he's serious.

936
01:21:42.310 --> 01:21:43.920 line:82%
Have you gone mad?

937
01:21:45.830 --> 01:21:48.420 line:82%
Sid, listen...

938
01:21:50.760 --> 01:21:55.460 line:82%
I'm no great expert on love,
but isn't this a bit too much?

939
01:21:58.190 --> 01:22:03.010 line:82%
- Because she's older than me?
- No, well, that too!

940
01:22:03.630 --> 01:22:07.140 line:82%
Hold on. Why are we
even discussing this nonsense?

941
01:22:10.730 --> 01:22:13.650 line:82%
Because I thought you two
would understand me.

942
01:22:19.960 --> 01:22:21.200 line:82%
Hey, Sid!

943
01:22:21.790 --> 01:22:23.030 line:82%
Understand what?

944
01:22:24.860 --> 01:22:28.750 line:82%
You say you love a woman who's
fifteen years older than you.

945
01:22:29.290 --> 01:22:32.290 line:82%
She has a daughter.
She had a husband.

946
01:22:33.300 --> 01:22:35.260 line:82%
You just said that she has
a drinking problem.

947
01:22:35.350 --> 01:22:37.090 line:82%
- What are we supposed to understand?
- That...

948
01:22:37.180 --> 01:22:39.470 line:82%
That I love her despite all that.

949
01:22:40.000 --> 01:22:41.720 line:82%
Sid, just give it a thought.

950
01:22:42.320 --> 01:22:44.690 line:82%
- This isn't love. It's madness.
- No.

951
01:22:45.650 --> 01:22:46.730 line:82%
This is love.

952
01:22:49.580 --> 01:22:52.040 line:82%
I don't expect her to be mine or marry me.

953
01:22:52.240 --> 01:22:54.020 line:82%
I don't hope for that.

954
01:22:54.550 --> 01:22:57.480 line:82%
- Even if she doesn't love me, it's fine.
- Oh, I see.

955
01:22:59.070 --> 01:23:00.740 line:82%
Now I get it.

956
01:23:01.640 --> 01:23:05.030 line:82%
Remember, Sameer?
That's how it started for me too.

957
01:23:05.620 --> 01:23:09.260 line:82%
- What do you mean?
- Of course.

958
01:23:09.340 --> 01:23:13.380 line:82%
Sid, if that's how it is, I don't mind.

959
01:23:13.740 --> 01:23:15.750 line:82%
In fact she's perfect for you.

960
01:23:16.010 --> 01:23:20.340 line:82%
She's experienced, lives alone.
You see her every day too.

961
01:23:21.810 --> 01:23:24.430 line:82%
Sameer, learn from him.

962
01:23:24.500 --> 01:23:27.030 line:82%
Sid, it's a perfect choice...

963
01:23:31.800 --> 01:23:34.230 line:82%
What a perverted mind you have!

964
01:23:36.800 --> 01:23:41.530 line:82%
I'm telling you I love her
but you made a dirty joke out of it.

965
01:23:43.350 --> 01:23:45.110 line:82%
Grow up, Akash.

966
01:23:46.180 --> 01:23:49.370 line:82%
We don't have to agree on everything.

967
01:23:50.340 --> 01:23:54.360 line:82%
But there's a line in friendship
that mustn't be crossed, but you did.

968
01:23:56.860 --> 01:23:58.630 line:82%
And you know what, Akash?

969
01:23:59.550 --> 01:24:04.130 line:82%
At some point in life
we all experience true love.

970
01:24:05.840 --> 01:24:09.890 line:82%
Then all these things, like age,

971
01:24:11.080 --> 01:24:15.330 line:82%
do not matter.
They all seem trivial.

972
01:24:17.510 --> 01:24:20.980 line:82%
I pity you, Akash. You won't
understand all this today.

973
01:24:23.320 --> 01:24:27.110 line:82%
But one day you'll realize
that love cannot be planned.

974
01:24:28.490 --> 01:24:29.990 line:82%
It just happens.

975
01:24:36.210 --> 01:24:37.730 line:82%
Are you finished?

976
01:24:39.900 --> 01:24:40.900 line:82%
Yes.

977
01:24:47.520 --> 01:24:48.910 line:82%
Sameer, are you coming?

978
01:25:44.980 --> 01:25:46.470 line:82%
I still remember that night.

979
01:25:49.310 --> 01:25:50.350 line:82%
I...

980
01:25:50.890 --> 01:25:52.020 line:82%
I was shocked.

981
01:25:54.310 --> 01:25:56.810 line:82%
I never thought things would go that far.

982
01:26:02.900 --> 01:26:04.490 line:82%
I couldn't sleep that night.

983
01:26:05.610 --> 01:26:07.320 line:82%
Next morning, I went to see Akash.

984
01:26:18.830 --> 01:26:22.710 line:82%
I dream of rain

985
01:26:22.800 --> 01:26:27.050 line:82%
I dream of gardens
in the desert sand

986
01:26:27.130 --> 01:26:29.140 line:82%
I wake in pain

987
01:26:41.690 --> 01:26:42.860 line:82%
Are you okay?

988
01:26:47.000 --> 01:26:49.020 line:82%
These things happen between friends.

989
01:26:49.410 --> 01:26:53.040 line:82%
Let's go and meet Sid.
He must be disturbed, too.

990
01:26:55.080 --> 01:26:57.240 line:82%
You're sure to run into him somewhere.

991
01:26:57.330 --> 01:27:00.290 line:82%
What will you do then?
Ignore him?

992
01:27:02.480 --> 01:27:04.220 line:82%
Akash, are you you listening to me?

993
01:27:06.720 --> 01:27:08.260 line:82%
You're coming to meet Sid.

994
01:27:10.090 --> 01:27:11.970 line:82%
- Come on.
- Leave me alone, Sameer!

995
01:27:12.810 --> 01:27:14.260 line:82%
Just get the hell out of here!

996
01:27:36.890 --> 01:27:39.080 line:82%
Good morning, Mrs. Sinha.
I'd like to see Sid.

997
01:27:39.390 --> 01:27:41.550 line:82%
- He's gone.
- Where?

998
01:27:41.630 --> 01:27:44.430 line:82%
To Kasauli.
He got a call last evening

999
01:27:44.500 --> 01:27:47.920 line:82%
and they said his application
was accepted and...

1000
01:27:50.490 --> 01:27:51.930 line:82%
What happened, Sameer?

1001
01:27:52.780 --> 01:27:55.060 line:82%
- Is everything alright?
- What?

1002
01:27:56.090 --> 01:27:59.020 line:82%
Of course. I'll leave now.

1003
01:27:59.450 --> 01:28:00.690 line:82%
Bye, Mrs. Sinha.

1004
01:28:05.970 --> 01:28:09.530 line:82%
I didn't realize that things
would never be the same again.

1005
01:28:10.100 --> 01:28:11.820 line:82%
You went to Kasauli.

1006
01:28:12.110 --> 01:28:14.810 line:82%
A week later Akash left for Australia.

1007
01:28:22.370 --> 01:28:24.540 line:82%
- Bye, mom.
- Bye.

1008
01:28:26.040 --> 01:28:27.750 line:82%
Take care of yourself.

1009
01:28:27.860 --> 01:28:31.150 line:82%
I hope you remember who
you're meeting at the Sydney airport?

1010
01:28:31.240 --> 01:28:34.680 line:82%
Mr. Mehta.
Relax, Dad. I remember.

1011
01:28:35.120 --> 01:28:36.390 line:82%
Good luck.

1012
01:28:40.070 --> 01:28:43.270 line:82%
- I'll go now. I'll call you from there.
- Okay.

1013
01:28:45.870 --> 01:28:48.600 line:82%
- I wanted to tell you something.
- What?

1014
01:28:49.750 --> 01:28:52.450 line:82%
Just that I always

1015
01:28:53.480 --> 01:28:56.870 line:82%
made fun of your romantic affairs.

1016
01:28:58.830 --> 01:29:02.580 line:82%
I never thought how you'd feel.

1017
01:29:04.430 --> 01:29:08.000 line:82%
You know I was just kidding,
don't you?

1018
01:29:09.760 --> 01:29:11.260 line:82%
Of course.

1019
01:29:11.340 --> 01:29:14.930 line:82%
Don't worry. You weren't
the only one who was kidding.

1020
01:29:16.000 --> 01:29:17.460 line:82%
Remember Shalini?

1021
01:29:18.350 --> 01:29:21.470 line:82%
I remember her as well as Rohit's punch.

1022
01:29:22.430 --> 01:29:25.980 line:82%
- I knew she was Rohit's fiancee.
- What?

1023
01:29:26.480 --> 01:29:29.520 line:82%
- Why didn't you stop me then?
- Have a nice flight.

1024
01:29:31.360 --> 01:29:33.190 line:82%
You son of a gun!

1025
01:29:49.930 --> 01:29:51.250 line:82%
Hi.

1026
01:29:55.820 --> 01:29:57.340 line:82%
I said, "Hi."

1027
01:29:58.810 --> 01:30:00.180 line:82%
Hi.

1028
01:30:01.030 --> 01:30:02.470 line:82%
Where are you going?

1029
01:30:03.500 --> 01:30:05.350 line:82%
This flight goes to Sydney.

1030
01:30:05.620 --> 01:30:08.960 line:82%
- But where are you going?
- Sydney.

1031
01:30:09.490 --> 01:30:12.060 line:82%
How strange! All three of us
are going to Sydney.

1032
01:30:12.920 --> 01:30:15.620 line:82%
- Three?
- Yes. You, me and this flight!

1033
01:30:19.550 --> 01:30:21.590 line:82%
I hope you know you're crazy!

1034
01:30:21.960 --> 01:30:23.450 line:82%
Thank you.

1035
01:30:24.130 --> 01:30:25.500 line:82%
Thanks.

1036
01:30:27.140 --> 01:30:28.930 line:82%
Well, listen...

1037
01:30:29.940 --> 01:30:33.420 line:82%
I'm really sorry about that night.

1038
01:30:34.480 --> 01:30:36.020 line:82%
I was just kidding.

1039
01:30:36.340 --> 01:30:39.050 line:82%
- It's okay.
- Really?

1040
01:30:40.250 --> 01:30:41.680 line:82%
Good.

1041
01:30:43.920 --> 01:30:46.510 line:82%
- So you...
- So you...

1042
01:30:47.320 --> 01:30:50.060 line:82%
- Go ahead.
- Why are you going to Sydney?

1043
01:30:50.850 --> 01:30:53.900 line:82%
Dad wants me to manage
his business there.

1044
01:30:54.210 --> 01:30:56.280 line:82%
Now let's see how long it lasts!

1045
01:30:56.730 --> 01:30:59.580 line:82%
- And you?
- My uncle lives there.

1046
01:30:59.870 --> 01:31:02.530 line:82%
My mother's brother.
I'm going to meet him.

1047
01:31:02.760 --> 01:31:04.420 line:82%
He's not like Rohit, is he?

1048
01:31:06.390 --> 01:31:07.540 line:82%
No, thanks.

1049
01:31:07.990 --> 01:31:11.330 line:82%
- What does he do?
- He's a photographer.

1050
01:31:12.560 --> 01:31:14.290 line:82%
Have you been to Sydney before?

1051
01:31:15.820 --> 01:31:17.770 line:82%
Do you always ask so many questions?

1052
01:31:17.860 --> 01:31:18.980 line:82%
Yes.

1053
01:31:19.060 --> 01:31:20.840 line:82%
Have you been to Sydney before?

1054
01:31:20.930 --> 01:31:22.260 line:82%
Yes.

1055
01:31:22.350 --> 01:31:24.800 line:82%
Good. You can show me around.

1056
01:31:24.910 --> 01:31:28.560 line:82%
Hold on. Don't you know
anyone else there?

1057
01:31:28.850 --> 01:31:30.980 line:82%
There's Mr. Mehta.

1058
01:31:32.140 --> 01:31:34.490 line:82%
Do you think I'll enjoy
hanging out with him?

1059
01:31:35.590 --> 01:31:37.780 line:82%
Please. Come on.

1060
01:31:38.700 --> 01:31:40.050 line:82%
I already said I'm sorry.

1061
01:31:40.140 --> 01:31:42.320 line:82%
Okay. But I'll have to ask my uncle.

1062
01:31:42.720 --> 01:31:46.770 line:82%
Yes, sure.
But I don't think he'll refuse.

1063
01:31:46.870 --> 01:31:48.120 line:82%
Why?

1064
01:31:48.200 --> 01:31:50.000 line:82%
Because I have a present for him.

1065
01:31:55.970 --> 01:31:57.680 line:82%
Tada!

1066
01:32:00.920 --> 01:32:03.220 line:82%
- Oh... please.
- Smile.

1067
01:32:14.490 --> 01:32:16.110 line:82%
Hey, Shalini!

1068
01:32:18.680 --> 01:32:20.290 line:82%
- Hi.
- Hi, how are you?

1069
01:32:20.370 --> 01:32:22.090 line:82%
Uncle Mahesh, how are you?

1070
01:32:22.170 --> 01:32:24.430 line:82%
I'm fine.
But stop calling me uncle.

1071
01:32:24.530 --> 01:32:27.780 line:82%
You've grown up now.
We're almost the same age.

1072
01:32:28.400 --> 01:32:30.120 line:82%
Oh, Akash.

1073
01:32:31.700 --> 01:32:34.300 line:82%
Akash, Uncle Mahesh.
Uncle Mahesh, Akash.

1074
01:32:34.390 --> 01:32:35.390 line:82%
I'm Mahesh.

1075
01:32:35.480 --> 01:32:36.800 line:82%
- Hi, Mahesh.
- Hi.

1076
01:32:36.880 --> 01:32:38.160 line:82%
Let's go.

1077
01:32:38.220 --> 01:32:40.370 line:82%
- Are you in Sydney on a business trip?
- Yes.

1078
01:32:40.450 --> 01:32:43.510 line:82%
Dad's packed me off here
to run our export business.

1079
01:32:43.590 --> 01:32:45.420 line:82%
Export business sounds very boring, man.

1080
01:32:45.500 --> 01:32:46.790 line:82%
I agree.

1081
01:32:46.860 --> 01:32:49.280 line:82%
- I'd prefer something more adventurous.
- I see.

1082
01:32:49.370 --> 01:32:51.170 line:82%
For instance wildlife photography.

1083
01:32:51.260 --> 01:32:53.100 line:82%
You like photography?

1084
01:32:53.340 --> 01:32:56.430 line:82%
Mom says the first word I uttered

1085
01:32:56.500 --> 01:32:59.380 line:82%
wasn't "mom'"or "dad,"
but "camera."

1086
01:33:00.220 --> 01:33:02.760 line:82%
- Excuse me. Akash?
- Yes?

1087
01:33:02.840 --> 01:33:05.020 line:82%
- Steve.
- Steve?

1088
01:33:05.090 --> 01:33:07.620 line:82%
Satyadev Mehta.
- Oh, Mr. Mehta!

1089
01:33:07.680 --> 01:33:08.910 line:82%
I'm so sorry. Hi.

1090
01:33:08.980 --> 01:33:12.340 line:82%
I've arranged for a car.
I'll take your baggage.

1091
01:33:12.420 --> 01:33:14.040 line:82%
Sure.

1092
01:33:14.580 --> 01:33:17.070 line:82%
I'm going, Shalini. Bye, Mahesh.

1093
01:33:17.140 --> 01:33:18.350 line:82%
Bye, Akash.

1094
01:33:18.440 --> 01:33:22.820 line:82%
If you need anything in Sydney,
here's my card.

1095
01:33:23.470 --> 01:33:26.170 line:82%
- Call me.
- Thank you. Bye.

1096
01:33:26.270 --> 01:33:27.930 line:82%
- Bye.
- Bye.

1097
01:33:45.620 --> 01:33:47.520 line:82%
I hope you like it.

1098
01:33:48.360 --> 01:33:50.120 line:82%
It's beautiful.

1099
01:33:50.520 --> 01:33:52.480 line:82%
- Thank you.
- Well, I'll leave.

1100
01:33:52.560 --> 01:33:54.130 line:82%
You'd better get some rest.

1101
01:33:54.210 --> 01:33:56.640 line:82%
I'll send the driver
to pick you up tomorrow.

1102
01:33:56.860 --> 01:33:58.380 line:82%
- Thank you, Steve.
- Okay.

1103
01:33:58.460 --> 01:34:00.290 line:82%
- Good night.
- Good night.

1104
01:34:17.770 --> 01:34:18.850 line:82%
Yes, Dad.

1105
01:34:19.770 --> 01:34:21.150 line:82%
Yes.

1106
01:34:21.690 --> 01:34:23.230 line:82%
I'll tell Mr. Mehta

1107
01:34:24.570 --> 01:34:25.690 line:82%
How's Mom?

1108
01:34:29.530 --> 01:34:32.240 line:82%
Give her my love.
Alright, bye.

1109
01:34:36.420 --> 01:34:38.290 line:82%
Joan, could you send Mr. Mehta in please?

1110
01:34:44.460 --> 01:34:46.870 line:82%
- Yes, Akash.
- Mr. Mehta...

1111
01:34:47.140 --> 01:34:48.840 line:82%
Oh, I'm sorry. Steve!

1112
01:34:50.550 --> 01:34:52.940 line:82%
Dad wants you to send him
a copy of the new contract.

1113
01:34:53.040 --> 01:34:54.180 line:82%
Okay.

1114
01:34:54.530 --> 01:34:55.890 line:82%
Steve.

1115
01:34:56.160 --> 01:34:58.510 line:82%
- You're coming to the meeting tomorrow?
- Of course.

1116
01:34:58.600 --> 01:35:01.650 line:82%
Good. Could you give me
all the files on that company?

1117
01:35:01.730 --> 01:35:03.680 line:82%
I'd like to study them before the meeting.

1118
01:35:03.770 --> 01:35:05.550 line:82%
I'll send them in right away.

1119
01:35:05.630 --> 01:35:06.840 line:82%
Oh, and Steve...

1120
01:35:08.460 --> 01:35:09.740 line:82%
Yes, Akash?

1121
01:35:10.990 --> 01:35:12.730 line:82%
Is there a good restaurant nearby?

1122
01:35:21.970 --> 01:35:23.210 line:82%
Thank you.

1123
01:35:25.800 --> 01:35:28.800 line:82%
- Wow, I'm really hungry.
- Yes.

1124
01:35:32.610 --> 01:35:34.890 line:82%
Wow, heaven.

1125
01:35:37.020 --> 01:35:38.640 line:82%
Thanks for coming, Shalini.

1126
01:35:38.720 --> 01:35:41.020 line:82%
To be alone in a new city
can be boring.

1127
01:35:41.600 --> 01:35:43.210 line:82%
But you aren't alone.

1128
01:35:43.550 --> 01:35:45.100 line:82%
Did I say I was bored?

1129
01:35:47.130 --> 01:35:48.480 line:82%
So strange.

1130
01:35:49.120 --> 01:35:53.200 line:82%
I never imagined we'd be talking
like this one day.

1131
01:35:55.820 --> 01:35:57.370 line:82%
Especially, after what happened.

1132
01:35:59.950 --> 01:36:01.250 line:82%
How is Rohit?

1133
01:36:02.150 --> 01:36:04.880 line:82%
He's fine. I spoke to him this morning.

1134
01:36:05.640 --> 01:36:09.550 line:82%
I told him I met you on the flight and...

1135
01:36:12.700 --> 01:36:14.520 line:82%
And he doesn't like you
seeing me, right?

1136
01:36:15.470 --> 01:36:16.590 line:82%
Well...

1137
01:36:20.040 --> 01:36:21.810 line:82%
But you're still here. Why?

1138
01:36:22.050 --> 01:36:24.760 line:82%
You don't know Rohit.

1139
01:36:24.840 --> 01:36:27.090 line:82%
He doesn't like me seeing any man.

1140
01:36:27.650 --> 01:36:28.940 line:82%
He's very possessive.

1141
01:36:29.780 --> 01:36:31.360 line:82%
But Rohit is a good guy.

1142
01:36:31.840 --> 01:36:33.470 line:82%
He has a few flaws.

1143
01:36:33.570 --> 01:36:37.010 line:82%
Don't we all have them?
Me, you...

1144
01:36:37.630 --> 01:36:40.050 line:82%
Me? And flaws?

1145
01:36:42.220 --> 01:36:43.910 line:82%
Tell me about yourself.

1146
01:36:45.180 --> 01:36:50.130 line:82%
- What do you want know?
- Let's see. Girlfriends?

1147
01:36:52.430 --> 01:36:55.840 line:82%
Of course I have them.
But they only last two weeks.

1148
01:36:56.450 --> 01:36:58.720 line:82%
Then another girlfriend for two weeks.

1149
01:36:59.400 --> 01:37:01.360 line:82%
- Then another for the next two weeks...
- Hold on.

1150
01:37:01.690 --> 01:37:06.540 line:82%
I understand your dating habits.
But I don't know why it's so.

1151
01:37:08.020 --> 01:37:11.360 line:82%
I've seen many of my friends
with their sweethearts.

1152
01:37:11.860 --> 01:37:14.740 line:82%
They have everything
but love for each other.

